<div class='foot section' id='footer-1'><div class='widget Profile' id='Profile1'>
<h2>About Me</h2>
<div class='widget-content'>
<a href='http://www.blogger.com/profile/02989747964139164372'><img alt='My Photo' class='profile-img' height='60' src='http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-1TBgcvtGmI4/TtqsaEN53sI/AAAAAAAAADw/a6pYgn0OUQw/s220/Home%2BPage%2BClouds%2BPhoto.jpg' width='80'/></a>
<dl class='profile-datablock'>
<dt class='profile-data'>
<a class='profile-name-link' href='http://www.blogger.com/profile/02989747964139164372' rel='author'>
Albert Rommal
</a>
</dt>
<dd class='profile-textblock'>I am the co-pastor of Northwest Baptist Church in Phoenix, Arizona. I've been a pastor and elder for over 16 years and helped plant two churches.  More importantly, I am an awful sinner deserving of His wrath, but instead receiving of the riches of His free grace.




The Doctrines of Grace are some of the sweetest truths I ever beheld and am thankful to God for them.  I firmly believe that I am only in Christ because God chose me from the foundation for this purpose (Eph 1:4).  

In addition, I believe the mission of the church is to make disciples which are in belief and behavior consistent with those our Lord described. (Matt 28:18-20)

www.nwbaptistchurch.org</dd>
</dl>
